      <section eId="sec_3_4_40">
        <num>3-4-40</num>
        <content>
          <p>Licenses for the package sale of distilled spirits shall be authorized only in those counties and municipalities in which the issuance of such licenses is approved by a referendum election as provided in this article.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1937-38, Ex. Sess., p. 103, § 4; Ga. L. 1972, p. 207, § 3; Code 1933, § 5A-2301, enacted by Ga. L. 1980, p. 1573, § 1; Ga. L. 2017, p. 820, § 2/HB 485.)</p>
          <p>The 2017 amendment,
      effective May 9, 2017, in this Code section, substituted "Licenses for the package sale of distilled spirits shall be" for "Licenses provided for in this article are" near the beginning and substituted "by a referendum election" for "by referendum" near the end.</p>
        </content>
      </section>
